Description: Sebastian is a loyal butler who moves easily from dinner parties to the underworld. Is he too good to be true? Is he even human? In this volume: a mystery at the circus.
Title: BLACK BUTLER, VOL. 6
Author: Yana Toboso

Description: Political intrigue abounds! What happened between Danzo, the leader of Konoha, and his brother, Itachi? And where does Naruto fit in?
Title: NARUTO, VOL. 51
Author: Masashi Kishimoto

Description: Negi, the boy wizard, learns the truth about his parents. Will he now seek revenge? Is dark magic tainting him?
Title: NEGIMA! MAGISTER NEGI MAGI, VOL. 30
Author: Ken Akamatsu

Description: Misao Harada can see into a magical realm where she is the bride demon of prophecy. How will she survive the pursuit of demons who want the power in her blood?
Title: BLACK BIRD, VOL. 9
Author: Kanoko Sakurakoji

Description: Cross Academy has day and evening students, but the latter have a secret: they are vampires.
Title: VAMPIRE KNIGHT, VOL. 12
Author: Matsuri Hino

Description: From the publisher: "A high-speed Turbo Duel through the streets of Satellite brings Yusei Fudo and his friend Sect face-to-face with an urban legend incarnate!"
Title: YU-GI-OH! 5D'S, VOL. 1
Author: Masahiro Hikokubo

Description: Oz, who is condemned for a mysterious sin, reunites with his sister, but evil lurks around the corner.
Title: PANDORA HEARTS, VOL. 6
Author: Jun Mochizuki

Description: Amu has three guardians who are helping her discover her true self. In this volume: the guardians disappear on the eve of graduation and Amu must find them.
Title: SHUGO CHARA!, VOL. 11
Author: Peach-Pit

Description: Rin Okumura joins an exorcist academy in order to control his inner demon. Will his classmates find out about his satanic bloodline?
Title: BLUE EXORCIST, VOL. 1
Author: Kazue Kato

Description: Hikage Sumino is an eighth grader with no self-esteem and whose social interaction comes from her blog. In this volume, when her worlds intersect, she learns about "friendship, love and forgiveness."
Title: I AM HERE!, VOL. 2
Author: Ema Toyama
